==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intercostal
<hw>In`ter*cos"tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat. &
Physiol.)</fld> <def>Between the ribs; pertaining to, or produced by,
the parts between the ribs; <as>as, <ex>intercostal</ex> respiration, in
which the chest is alternately enlarged and contracted by the
<ex>intercostal</ex> muscles</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intercourse</ent>⟦br⟧
